thread.title: La Salle pummels Winton Woods to move to 8-1

title: La Salle pummels Winton Woods to move to 8-1
text:
La Salle pummels Winton Woods to move to 8-1 La Salle quarterback Nick Watson reacts following the Lancers' 49-14 rout of Winton Woods on Friday night. Mike Dyer , mdyer@enquirer.com 12:32 a.m. EDT October 24, 2015 Buy Photo La Salle running back Jeremy Larkin (28) scores on a 70-yard touchdown catch and run in the first quarter during the high school football game between the Winton Woods Warriors and La Salle Lancers, Friday, Oct. 23, 2015, at La Salle High School in Green Township, Ohio. (Photo: The Enquirer/Kareem Elgazzar) Buy Photo 23 CONNECT 12 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Kyle Farwick's favorite part of Lancer Stadium is when the community gets together on game night. 
Josh Gebing likes to remember the games in which the Lancers dominated certain opponents. 
"I love it a lot," senior quarterback Nick Watson said. "I wish I could restart the whole game over again, but..." 
The Lancers weren't very sentimental for the two hours after kickoff. 
Larkin, a University of Cincinnati verbal commit, scored four touchdowns as the Lancers defeated Winton Woods, 49-14.
